"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150878","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-24","<p>As specified in the Public Appointments Order in Council 2019, my right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence is responsible for public appointments to the following public bodies and offices:</p><p>Armed Forces Pay Review Body</p><p>Defence Nuclear Safety Committee</p><p>Independent Medical Expert Group</p><p>Independent Monitoring Board for the Military Corrective Training Centre</p><p>Nuclear Research Advisory Council</p><p>Oil and Pipelines Agency</p><p>Royal Air Force Museum</p><p>Science Advisory Committee on the Medical Implications of Less-Lethal Weapons</p><p>Service Complaints Ombudsman</p><p>Single Source Regulations Office</p><p>Veterans Advisory and Pensions Committees</p>","Plymouth, Moor View","Johnny Mercer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150878/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-24T14:27:29.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150878/answer","Biography information for Johnny Mercer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150878/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-21","Ministry of Defence: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which public appointments he is responsible for.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","2669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150879","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-10-28","<p>The public appointments that the Department is responsible for making are set out in the Schedule to the Public Appointments Order in Council 2019.</p><p><a href="https://publicappointments.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2019-Public-Appointments-Order-In-Council.pdf" target="_blank">https://publicappointments.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2019-Public-Appointments-Order-In-Council.pdf</a></p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150879/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-28T16:51:48.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150879/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150879/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-21","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, which public appointments he is responsible for.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","2670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150880","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-10-24","<p>As set out in Article 2(2) Bodies and Offices Regulated by the Commissioner for Public Appointments of the Order in Council 2019, the Secretary of State for Justice is responsible for the following appointments:</p><p> </p><p><strong>Advisory Committees on Justices of the Peace</strong></p><p><strong>Advisory Council on Conscientious Objectors (This is an MoD Public Body - It was established in 1970 but its history can be traced back to the tribunals set up by the National Service (Armed Forces) Act 1939. The 1970 arrangements included an agreement that, to make sure of the independence of the committee, these appointments should be made by the Lord Chancellor). </strong></p><p><strong>Chair of the National Council of Prisoner Escort and Custody Services Lay Observers</strong></p><p><strong>Children and Family Court Advisory and Support Service (Cafcass)</strong></p><p><strong>Civil Justice Council (CJC)</strong></p><p><strong>Civil Procedure Rule Committee</strong></p><p><strong>Commissioner for Victims and Witnesses</strong></p><p><strong>Court Examiners</strong></p><p><strong>Court of Protection Visitors</strong></p><p><strong>Criminal Cases Review Commission (CCRC)</strong></p><p><strong>Criminal Procedure Rule Committee</strong></p><p><strong>Family Procedure Rule Committee</strong></p><p><strong>Her Majesty's Chief Inspector of Prisons for England and Wales</strong></p><p><strong>Her Majesty's Chief Inspector of Probation</strong></p><p><strong>Independent Advisory Panel on Deaths in Custody</strong></p><p><strong>Independent Monitoring Board of any prison or young offender institution (IMBs)</strong></p><p><strong>Insolvency Rules Committee (This is a BEIS Public Body. However, legislation explains that the Lord Chancellor is responsible for making the public appointments).</strong></p><p><strong>Judicial Appointments and Conduct Ombudsman (JACO)</strong></p><p><strong>Judicial Appointments Commission (JAC)</strong></p><p><strong>Judicial Pension Board, independent Chair and independent members only</strong></p><p><strong>Law Commission, except for the Chair</strong></p><p><strong>Legal Services Board (LSB)</strong></p><p><strong>Multi-Agency Public Protection Arrangements Lay Advisers (MAPPA)</strong></p><p><strong>National Chair of the Independent Monitoring Boards (IMB)</strong></p><p><strong>National Mental Capacity Forum, Chair Only</strong></p><p><strong>Non-Judicial Members of Disciplinary Panels of the Judicial Conduct Investigations Office (JCIO)</strong></p><p><strong>Parole Board for England and Wales, except for judicial members</strong></p><p><strong>Persons appointed by the Lord Chancellor under section 2 of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012 (Legal Aid Agency: Funding and Costs Appeals Review Panel Members and Very High Cost Cases Appeals Panel Members)</strong></p><p><strong>Prisoner Escort and Custody Services Lay Observers (PECS)</strong></p><p><strong>Prisons and Probation Ombudsman (PPO)</strong></p><p><strong>Prison Service Pay Review Body (PSPRB)</strong></p><p><strong>Sentencing Council for England and Wales</strong></p><p><strong>Tribunal Procedure Committee (TPC)</strong></p><p><strong>Youth Justice Board for England and Wales (YJB)</strong></p>","Croydon South","Chris Philp","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150880/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-24T13:46:29.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150880/answer","Biography information for Chris Philp","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150880/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-10-21","Ministry of Justice: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which public appointments he is responsible for.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","2671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150881","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-10-28","<p>As set out in the Public Appointments Order in Council 2019, Northern Ireland Office ministers are responsible for the following appointments:</p><p> </p><p>Boundary Commission for Northern Ireland</p><p>Chief Electoral Officer for Northern Ireland</p><p>Equality Commission for Northern Ireland</p><p>Northern Ireland Human Rights Commission</p><p>Parades Commission for Northern Ireland</p><p> </p><p>In addition, under the terms of the Executive Formation and Exercise of Functions Act 2018, and in the absence of Northern Ireland Ministers, the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland is temporarily responsible for approving a number of critical Northern Ireland appointments as and when they arise.</p><p> </p>","Skipton and Ripon","Julian Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150881/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-28T11:48:04.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150881/answer","Biography information for Julian Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150881/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-10-21","Northern Ireland Office: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, which public appointments his Department is responsible for.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","2672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150882","Scotland Office","false","2019-10-29","<p>The public appointments that the Office of the Secretary of State for Scotland is responsible for making are set out in the Schedule to the Public Appointments Order in Council 2019:</p><p><a href="https://publicappointments.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2019-Public-Appointments-Order-In-Council.pdf" target="_blank">https://publicappointments.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2019-Public-Appointments-Order-In-Council.pdf</a></p>","Dumfries and Galloway","Mr Alister Jack","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150882/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-29T11:07:43.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150882/answer","Biography information for Mr Alister Jack","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150882/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2019-10-21","Scotland Office: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, which public appointments he is responsible for.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","2673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150883","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-24","<p>We strongly condemn the recent incidents of racism in sport both at home and abroad. There is no place anywhere for racism in sport and we want it stamped out at every level of competition.</p><p> </p><p>Government ministers and officials regularly meet the football authorities and other sports governing bodies, including the Football Association and Badminton England, to discuss a wide range of issues, including how we can work together to tackle racism.</p>","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150883/answer",,,,,"2754","2019-10-24T09:17:36.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150883/answer","Biography information for Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150883/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-21","Football and Badminton: Racial Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of levels of racism in local (a) football and (b) badminton clubs.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","2755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150884","Leader of the House","false","2019-10-24","<p>The Office of the Leader of the House of Commons sits within the Cabinet Office. The public appointments that the Cabinet Office is responsible for making are set out in the Schedule to the Public Appointments Order in Council 2019. This is available at: <a href="https://publicappointments.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2019-Public-Appointments-Order-In-Council.pdf" target="_blank">https://publicappointments.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2019-Public-Appointments-Order-In-Council.pdf</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","North East Somerset","Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150884/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-24T16:57:12.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150884/answer","Biography information for Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150884/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2019-10-21","Leader of the House of Commons: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, which public appointments he is responsible for.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","2674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150885","Wales Office","false","2019-10-29","<p>The Secretary of State for Wales is not responsible for making any public appointments.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150885/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-29T17:20:04.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150885/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150885/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2019-10-21","Wales Office: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, which public appointments he is responsible for.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","2675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150886","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-10-24","<p>​The British Government is in close touch with the German Government regarding their respective immigration arrangements, including provisions for future mobility in a No Deal scenario. The German Parliament is also currently considering a Brexit Residence Transition Law which would come into effect in a No Deal scenario to ensure that all British Nationals and their family members who exercised freedom of movement rights before exit day receive a residence permit. British Nationals moving to Germany after exit day in the event of No Deal would need to follow German immigration guidelines.</p>","Tamworth","Christopher Pincher","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150886/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-24T14:37:51.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150886/answer","Biography information for Christopher Pincher","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150886/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-10-21","Germany: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with her German counterpart on the effect on a UK citizen marrying a German national who may move from the UK to Germany in the event that the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","2756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150887","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-10-24","<p>My Rt. Hon. friend the Lord Chancellor and Secretary of State for Justice Robert Buckland has responded to the letter from hon. Member for Enfield North, on behalf of the Prime Minister.</p>","Croydon South","Chris Philp","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150887/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-24T15:32:53.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150887/answer","Biography information for Chris Philp","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150887/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-10-21","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he plans to respond to the letter from hon. Member for Enfield North of 27 August 2019 on the Government's urgent sentencing review.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","2637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150888","Department for Education","false","2019-10-24","<p>The number of looked after children by placement since 2015 are published in Table A2 of the statistical release ‘Children looked after in England including adoption’, available here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption-2017-to-2018</a>.</p>","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150888/answer",,,,,,"2019-10-24T14:41:32.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150888/answer","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150888/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-10-21","Children in Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the number of looked after children in children's homes in each year since 2015.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","2685"
